label.value: Pallor of dorsal columns of the spinal cord

definition.value: An abnormally pale appearance of the dorsal portion of the gray substance of the spinal cord. This finding can be observed by histological examination.

label.value: Developmental stagnation at onset of seizures

definition.value: Developmental defect characterized by a small and malformed corpus callosum.

label.value: Sensorimotor polyneuropathy affecting arms more than legs
Intraaxonal accumulation of curvilinear autofluorescent lipopigment storage material

definition.value: Relatively short-lived periods of psychosis are characterized by the sudden onset of severe disturbances in perception, thinking, and behavior. These episodes typically last for a brief duration, generally ranging from a few days to a few weeks, and are often triggered by a significant stressor or traumatic event.
